# Wasteland Briefing Model v3 — "Deep-Thin with mHC"
#
# Combines BriefingV2's deep-thin architecture (40 layers, dim=768)
# with Manifold-Constrained Hyper-Connections for stable cross-layer
# information flow.
#
# Rationale from mHC paper (DeepSeek, arXiv:2512.24880v2):
# - HC expands residual stream width by factor n, enabling richer
#   cross-layer communication without changing per-layer FLOPs
# - Unconstrained HC causes signal explosion (3000x gain at 60 layers)
# - mHC constrains the mixing matrix to doubly stochastic (Birkhoff polytope)
#   via Sinkhorn-Knopp, bounding composite gain to ~1.6x
# - At 27B scale: +2.1% BBH, +2.3% DROP over HC, 6.7% training overhead
#
# Why this model specifically:
# - 40 layers is exactly where mHC shines (deep networks benefit most)
# - n=4 expansion on dim=768 means 4*768=3072 stream width — cheap
# - The doubly stochastic constraint guarantees stability at any depth
# - Fine-tuning variant: freeze backbone, train only mHC params (~0.1%)
#
# Architecture:
# - 40 layers, dim=768, 12 heads, 6 KV heads (GQA 2:1)
# - SwiGLU FFN with 2x expansion
# - RMSNorm (pre-norm)
# - mHC wrapping both attention and FFN sublayers (n=4)
# - Sinkhorn-Knopp with 20 iterations for H_res projection
#
# Estimated params: ~300M base + ~0.3M mHC params

/// Attention sublayer (unwrapped — mHC wraps this)
neuron AttentionSublayer(dim, num_heads, kv_heads):
    in: [batch, seq, dim]
    out: [batch, seq, dim]
    graph:
        in ->
            RMSNorm(dim)
            GroupedQueryAttention(dim, num_heads, kv_heads)
            out


/// FFN sublayer (unwrapped — mHC wraps this)
neuron FFNSublayer(dim, d_ff):
    in: [batch, seq, dim]
    out: [batch, seq, dim]
    graph:
        in ->
            RMSNorm(dim)
            SwiGLU(dim, d_ff)
            out


/// mHC-wrapped transformer block
/// Each sublayer gets its own ManifoldHyperConnect wrapper
/// which manages the n-wide residual stream and doubly stochastic mixing
neuron MHCBlock(dim, num_heads, kv_heads, d_ff, n, layer_idx):
    in: [batch, seq, n, dim]
    out: [batch, seq, n, dim]
    graph:
        # mHC wraps attention: manages residual stream expansion + mixing
        in -> ManifoldHyperConnect(AttentionSublayer(dim, num_heads, kv_heads), n, dim, layer_idx) -> mid
        # mHC wraps FFN: same stream, continues through FFN
        mid -> ManifoldHyperConnect(FFNSublayer(dim, d_ff), n, dim, layer_idx) -> out


/// Deep-thin briefing model with mHC — 40 layers, dim=768, n=4
neuron WastelandBriefingV3(vocab_size=32000, dim=768, num_heads=12, kv_heads=6, d_ff=1536, n=4, layers=40):
    in: [batch, seq]
    out: [batch, seq, vocab_size]
    context:
        # Each layer gets mHC wrapping with layer index for per-layer params
        stack = unroll(layers):
            block = MHCBlock(dim, num_heads, kv_heads, d_ff, n, layers)
    graph:
        in ->
            Embedding(vocab_size, dim)
            # TODO: Expand to n-wide stream here (need HCInit primitive)
            # For now, conceptual — the ManifoldHyperConnect handles expansion
            stack
            RMSNorm(dim)
            Linear(dim, vocab_size)
            out
